\n \nseparation\n \nbetween\n \ntrade\n \nunions\n \nand\n \nthe\n \nstate.\n&#xa0;\nWhy a civil servant e-mailed  the makers  of the Mary Queen of the High Street programme to ask which of the candidates for Portas Pilots  Channel 4 was interested in (Q 89-92)The\n \nquestion\n \nto\n \nthe\n \ntelevision\n \nproducers\n \nwas\n \nan\n \noff-the-cuff\n \nquery\n \nmade\n \nout\n \nof\n \ninterest.\n \nIt\n \nwas\n not\n \nasked\n \nto\n \nsuggest\n \nthere\n \ncould/would\n \nbe\n \nany\n \ninfluence\n \nover\n \nthe\n \ndecisions\n \nbeing\n \nmade\n \nabout the\n \nthree\n \nGLA\n \nfunded\n \nPortas\n \nPilots.\n \nThe\n \nDepartment\n \nhad\n \nno\n \ninfluence\n \nover\n \nwhich\n \nPilots\n \nwere selected\n \nby\n \nthe\n \nGLA\n \n-\n \nthe\n \napplications\n \nwere\n \nassessed\n \nand\n \nselected\n \nentirely\n \nindependently\n \nof \nDCLG.\n&#xa0;\nDuring\n \nCommittee\n \nyou\n \nalso\n \nasked\n \nif\n \nthe\n \nDepartment\n \nwas\n \naware\n \nof\n \nthe\n \nfee\n \nthat\n \nChannel\n \n4\n \nwas \npaying\n \nMary\n \nPortas\n.\n \nI\n \nundertook\n \nto\n \ncheck\n \nwhether\n \nor\n \nnot\n \nthere\n \nwas\n \nan\n \nawareness\n \nof\n \nthis\n \nwithin the\n \nDepartment.\n \nI\n \ncan\n \nconfirm\n \nthat\n \nofficials\n \nin the\n \nDepartment\n \nwere\n \nnot\n \naware\n \nof\n \nthe\n \nfinancial \narrangements\n \nbetween\n \nChannel\n \n4\n \nand\n \nMary\n \nPortas\n.\n&#xa0;\nReaction to National Housing  Federation figures about impact of increasing arrears and costs of collection on finance for affordable housing  (Q 119)We\n \nare\n \nworking\n \nclosely\n \nwith\n \nDWP\n \nto\n \ndevelop\n \nsafeguards\n \nto\n \nhelp\n \nprotect\n \nsocial\n \nlandlords'\n \nincome\n \nstreams\n \nif\n \na\n \ntenant\n \nfalls\n \nbehind\n \non\n \ntheir\n \nrent\n \nunder\n \ndirect\n \npayments\n \nof\n \nhousing\n \nsupport\n \nunder \nUniversal\n \nCredit. \n \nTogether\n \nwith\n \nDWP\n \nwe\n \nare\n \nundertaking\n \na\n \nseries\n \nof\n \nDemonstration\n \nProjects designed\n \nto\n \nassess\n \nthe\n \nimpact\n \nof\n \npaying\n \nthe\n \nhousing\n \nelement\n \nof\n \nUniversal\n \nCredit\n \ndirect\n \nto \nclaimants\n \nwith\n \nsix\n \npartnerships\n \nof\n \nlocal\n \nauthorities\n \nand\n \nhousing\n \nassociations.\n \nThese \ndemonstration\n \nprojects\n \nbegan\n \nin\n \nJune\n \n2012\n \nand\n \nwill\n \nrun\n \nuntil\n \nDecember\n \n2013.\n \nThe\n \nprojects\n \nare \nexploring\n \nthe\n \neffects\n \nof\n \ndirect\n \npayments\n \non\n \nlandlord\n \nand\n \ntenants,\n \ntesting\n \ndifferent\n \ntypes\n \nof \nsupport\n \nto\n \ntenants,\n \nand\n \ndifferent\n \nsafeguard\n \nmechanisms\n \nfor\n \nlandlords,\n \ne.g.\n \npayment\n \nswitch­ backs\n \nto\n \nlandlords\n \nif\n \na\n \ntenant\n \nfalls\n \ninto\n \narrears\n \nand\n \nearly\n \ninterventions.\n&#xa0;\nThe\n \nmost\n \nrecently\n \npublished\n \nfeedback\n \nfrom\n \nthe\n \nDemonstration\n \nProjects\n \nwas\n \nin\n \na\n \nMay\n \npress \nrelease\n \nfrom\n \nthe\n \nDepartment\n \nfor\n \nWork\n \nand\n \nPensions\n \nwith\n \nfindings\n \nfrom\n \nthe\n \nsix\n \nareas\n \ncovering \nthe first nine months of payment of housing benefits directly to tenants (available here:\n \nhttps://www.gov.uk/government/publications/direct-payment-demonstration-project-learning-and-payment-figures\n \n).  Figures in the May press release show 6,168 tenants received direct payments, the total level of rent charged stood at £19,204,022 and an improvement in the average rent collection rate to 94%- with levels of payments by tenants on the projects varying from 91% to 97%. (This compares to an average of 92% published in a December 2012 press release covering the first four months).  The demonstration projects are being independently evaluated (funded by DWP) by a research consortium, from the Centre for Regional Economic and Social Research (CRESR) at\n \nSheffield \nHallam\n University, \nthe Institute of Social Policy at the University of Oxford, and \nlpsos\n MORI (IM). The evaluation findings, including full rent account analysis and the operation of switch-backs are due to be published in a series of reports in 2014.\n&#xa0;\nIn response to a question from Bob Blackman on Call-In criteria, Peter Schofield referred the Committee to a \nWritten Ministerial Statement dated October 2012\n on this issue; a copy of that statement is attached to this letter for reference.\n28\n \nOctober \n2013\n&#xa0;\n"